11060009.text: After meeting with Pasa, I continued to practice with all my heart and without rest. I feel stronger than before, but seeing that Pasa is not contacting me, it seems that it is not yet the right time.

11060010.text: According to the guidance of the battle captain Han Su-min, we arrived at a place called the Haeryong Mountains, an unexplored area confirmed by this incident. Feeling a heavy and gloomy atmosphere, I looked around the joint post and found a familiar face. It was Arang.

11060011.text: I met Cha Nok-yun in the gray sky forest, where we had broken through the outpost of the Black Dawn and arrived. She was looking at the cart with only the grim traces left.

11060012.text: I followed Cha Nok-yun's guide and arrived at the search corps' post, but the situation there was not particularly good. Half of the crew members who went out to search the hills of predators were injured.

11060013.text: At the entrance of the dark forest, I found familiar black traces and torn clothes of Pungbaekmun. It was a look that could have guessed the horror of that time. But it was strange. Why couldn't even see a single corpse?

11060014.text: The place we arrived at to escape the pursuit of the Black Dawn was a shelter hidden at the foot of the Dark Forest. The man who introduced himself as Jang Ho-woon at that time seemed to know where the people who were kidnapped by the Black Dawn were, but immediately began to take refuge in the refugees.

11060015.text: I led the people who remained in the shelter and headed to the path of the soul following Jang Ho-un's guidance. As monsters were encamped along the way, Jang Ho-woon's face was stained with disappointment. \n\nAm I still doubting my abilities?

11060016.text: Jang Ho-woon, who was looking at the vast ruins, asked me a few things. He asked me to save the core and taffy rock. I'll explain it later, so it's clear that there's something inside...

11060017.text:
Where do you find the Biryu River in the polluted crater? 
I look around and there are only mutated beings. 

Then there is only one way.

11060018.text: I met an unexpected person at the base of the Bountiful rain forest that I stopped by for maintenance. It was Han Su-min, the captain of the battle at Pungbaekmun. \nShe said that she traveled all over the sea and moon continent to find me.

11060019.text: Biryuha, who is called the best sword of Pungbaek even if it is not known to other people…?

11060020.text: The gruesome trace that Chae Nok-yun was looking at was that of a troop supply unit heading to the search party’s outpost. The cart was shattered and all materials disappeared, and not far away, the body of a supply crew member was also found.

11060021.text: I followed Cha Nok-yun's guide and arrived at the search corps' post, but the situation there was not particularly good. Half of the crew members who went out to search the hills of predators were injured.

11060022.text: At the entrance of the dark forest, I found familiar black traces and torn clothes of Pungbaekmun. It was a look that could guess the horror of that time. But it was strange. Why can't even a single corpse be seen?

11060023.text: The place we arrived at to escape the pursuit of the Black Dawn was a shelter hidden at the foot of the Dark Forest. At that time, the man who introduced himself as Jang Ho-woon seemed to know where the people abducted by the Black Dawn were, but right now he had to take refuge in the shelter.

11060024.text: I led the people who remained in the shelter and headed to the path of the soul following Jang Ho-un's guidance. As monsters were encamped along the way, Jang Ho-woon's face was stained with disappointment. Aren't you still doubting my abilities? \n

11060025.text: Before going to the camp, Houn Jang had asked me to get the core and taffy rock of the bully. It was full of doubts, but he said he would explain it later, so he quickly got the materials and headed to the meeting place.

11060026.text: If I could fight with all my might… I thought while blocking Biryuha’s attack with a bright red eye beam. It was not easy to subdue Biryuha without getting hurt.
